description: Classic shoot-em-up action reprinted from actual Prize Comics and Magazine Enterprises comics of the 1950′s.Cover by Bill black, stories include The Latigo Kid in “Apache Uprising”, with art by John Severin; Wild Bill Pecos and the “Tombstone Bugle”, drawn by John Buscema (From Westerner #36, 1951), The Farg Kid in “Western Injustice”, by John Severin (Originally in Fargo Kid #2, 1955), The Haunted Horseman (M. E. ‘s Ghost Rider ) in “The invisible Death”, drawn by Dick Ayers ;photos and coverage of the 1989 Roy Rogers Festival inPortsmouth, Ohio and a back cover photo of Charles Starrett as The Durango Kid. Color cover, interiors black and white with tones. Standard comic book format.

volume.name: Undead Zombie Biker Chickens from Hell

description:
Marvel continues its innovative ROUGH CUT program with a special commemorative edition printing--for the very first time--Mark Waid's original plot and Ron Garney's untouched pencils for Captain America Sentinel of Liberty (1998) #1! Have you always wanted to be a fly on the wall in the House of Ideas as the raw ingredients to a hit comic entered the building? Now you can! It's all here in pure black and white: the plot as Waid turned it in and Garney's pristine pencils! Take a glimpse at Marvel history in the making! Match it up to the finished product to see how the magic all came together! And for all you aspiring artists, try taking Waid's plot and drawing your own issue--that is, if you dare go head-to-head with Garney!

Contains B&W sketches and background information.
name: Rough Cut
